<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1873-01-18T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1873-01-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="69" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d69">
                    <head>No. 375.<lb/><hi rend="italic">General <persName corresp="#p_DES1" type="from">Sickles</persName> to Mr. <persName corresp="#p_HF1" type="to">Fish</persName>.</hi></head>
                    <opener>
                        <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                    </opener>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Madrid</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1873-01-18"><hi rend="italic">January</hi> 18,
                            1873</date>.</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>Conference to-day with ministers of state and ultramar respecting embargoed
                        estates. It was agreed that the latter cable, captain-general of Cuba, and
                        the former cable, Admiral <persName>Polo</persName>, authorizing and
                        directing them to act in relation to pending cases and enjoining dispatch in
                        their proceeding. Minister of state expressed surprise and regret at
                        continued delay in cases of Mora, Mueses, Hernandez, Criado, and Mrs.
                        Mora.</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed><persName corresp="#p_DES1">SICKLES</persName>.</signed>
                    </closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>